1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,400
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:02,600
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:18,510
[Love Upon a Time Series]

4
00:00:18,540 --> 00:00:20,090
Fortune teller, it's me, Nakun...

5
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:25,140
My mission: Find out whatever happened
to the real Klao!

6
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:26,790
Is there a matter
you wish to discuss with him?

7
00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:28,190
I just want to visit the capital.

8
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:30,160
Have you sought his permission, Master?

9
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:31,520
Yes.

10
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,810
- Help! Help me!
- Be wary, my Lady!

11
00:00:33,830 --> 00:00:35,400
Help me!

12
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,090
- Help! Help me!
- Be wary, my Lady!

13
00:00:38,120 --> 00:00:40,640
Help me! I can bear it no more!

14
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:43,030
Help!!

15
00:00:43,350 --> 00:00:44,550
I can bear it no longer!

16
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:47,940
- Cease this harassment, Cherd.
- Mind your own affairs!!

17
00:00:49,010 --> 00:00:51,200
This matter is none of your concern!

18
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,340
Meddle not, or you shall face my wrath!

19
00:00:53,830 --> 00:00:56,030
- Be wary, my Lady.
- Trying to slip away?

20
00:00:56,060 --> 00:00:58,130
You dare escape my reach?!

21
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:00,210
- My Lady!
- Ah! My Lady!

22
00:01:02,030 --> 00:01:03,220
Who dares?!

23
00:01:07,930 --> 00:01:09,010
Klao...

24
00:01:15,220 --> 00:01:16,490
You... You...

25
00:01:17,330 --> 00:01:18,330
You know me?

26
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:20,070
You... You...

27
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:24,100
What?

28
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:25,370
What of me?

29
00:01:26,030 --> 00:01:27,030
Master Klao.

30
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:28,400
Let us return.

31
00:01:30,539 --> 00:01:32,539
Who's this dude? What's his name?

32
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,990
It is best not to meddle with him, Master.

33
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:39,560
Have I truly been forgotten by you, Klao?

34
00:01:40,509 --> 00:01:41,240
Yeah.

35
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:44,140
What means this commotion?!

36
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:49,940
Harn...

37
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:51,220
My Lord...

38
00:01:51,539 --> 00:01:52,530
Varna...

39
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:54,320
What has unfolded here?

40
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:57,180
My purse of coins slipped from my grasp.

41
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,360
This man managed to retrieve it.

42
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,530
Rather than return it graciously,

43
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:03,310
he chose to flirt

44
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,160
and seize my wrist.

45
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:08,870
However, this man

46
00:02:10,050 --> 00:02:11,500
came to my rescue.

47
00:02:12,850 --> 00:02:14,680
You have my deepest gratitude.

48
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:18,140
Dear Klao.

49
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:24,960
The common folk said that

50
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:26,740
you had gone missing.

51
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,050
Have you at last returned?

52
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:32,460
He knows me too?

53
00:02:37,180 --> 00:02:38,200
Dear Klao.

54
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,230
By what means have you returned?

55
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,150
Where did you disappear to?

56
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:45,250
Uh... I...

57
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:49,610
I...

58
00:02:53,370 --> 00:02:54,560
Think no more of it.

59
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:03,780
As for you, Cherd,

60
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:07,120
you shall suffer the consequences
for your insolent and lawless behavior.

61
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:10,370
My Lord, I...

62
00:03:10,670 --> 00:03:13,060
I did but jest with the lady.

63
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,540
There was no malice in my heart.

64
00:03:16,090 --> 00:03:18,340
I knew not that she was your lady.

65
00:03:20,420 --> 00:03:22,829
Varna is the daughter of mine own uncle.

66
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:24,840
She arrived from the city of Lavo
but yesterday!

67
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,730
Correct your understanding at once.

68
00:03:27,130 --> 00:03:27,950
Yes, my Lord.

69
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:33,100
Away with them, you two.

70
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:35,710
Their punishment shall await my arrival.

71
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:44,090
Varna, return to the manor at once.

72
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:47,120
The capital is vast and sprawling,
unlike the city of Lavo.

73
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,050
The deeper the dusk grows,
the more treacherous it is.

74
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,340
Yes, my Lord.

75
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,160
Yes, my Lord...

76
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:56,820
And you as well.

77
00:03:59,079 --> 00:03:59,890
Klao!

78
00:04:17,339 --> 00:04:18,209
Twin Phops...

79
00:04:18,899 --> 00:04:20,660
They're gonna tear me to shreds.

80
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:24,720
Who let you enter the scene at this moment?

81
00:04:26,530 --> 00:04:28,680
[Love Upon a Time Series]

82
00:05:38,290 --> 00:05:42,480
[Love Upon a Time Series]

83
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:04,810
We promised to be here together.

84
00:06:05,570 --> 00:06:06,970
Why, then, did you come here by yourself?

85
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:10,120
I came here with Chuay.

86
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,410
I didn't come here by myself.

87
00:06:14,710 --> 00:06:15,720
Yes, my Lord.

88
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,720
I have kept a close eye upon Master Klao.

89
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,430
He has always been within my reach.

90
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,710
He has not given himself over
to debauchery.

91
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,350
Halt.

92
00:06:26,170 --> 00:06:27,880
I have yet to utter a word of reproach.

93
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:30,520
My Lord.

94
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:33,580
I am Varna,

95
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,690
the daughter
of High Lord Dech Kraisor of Lavo.

96
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:40,320
Do you recognize me,
the lady standing before you, my Lord?

97
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:42,790
I do.

98
00:06:43,350 --> 00:06:44,920
You are of the Lord's kin.

99
00:06:45,070 --> 00:06:46,909
We met during the previous year,

100
00:06:47,409 --> 00:06:49,750
as I traveled in the retinue of my father
upon his royal service.

101
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:53,590
Oh...

102
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:56,190
Have you two been acquainted?

103
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:02,240
Only a few days have passed
since I came to this city, my Lord.

104
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:04,560
My father strictly enjoined me

105
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:07,410
to render my most humble respects
at the feet of High Lord Pichayabhakdi.

106
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,690
It is my firm intention
to make my journey on the morrow.

107
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,060
I had not anticipated that

108
00:07:12,290 --> 00:07:13,920
our paths would cross so soon.

109
00:07:27,110 --> 00:07:29,940
Righto, Mr. Sexy Boy of Ayothaya.

110
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,730
Everyone is swooning over you.

111
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:33,630
Chuay.

112
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:37,520
Escort your master to the pier at once.

113
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:39,220
Yes, my Lord.

114
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:41,700
Phop.

115
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:44,530
We've made our promise, haven't we?

116
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:45,930
Do go.

117
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,210
I have matters to attend upon the Lord.

118
00:07:52,159 --> 00:07:54,210
Master, let us leave.

119
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:55,630
I'm not leaving.

120
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,650
Master Klao!

121
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,270
Master!

122
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,220
This way, Master.

123
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,960
I beg of you, Master, follow me.

124
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:10,590
Gosh.

125
00:08:12,610 --> 00:08:13,680
Deary me, Master.

126
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,920
I have already cautioned you
that we ought to wait for the Lord.

127
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,390
It's fine.

128
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:20,560
At the end of the day, we met him here.

129
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,680
Master!

130
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:22,900
This is no jest.

131
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:25,510
Did I not warn you?
Trouble has arisen

132
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:27,170
of our meeting with Cherd.

133
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,080
What is there to worry about?

134
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:31,980
Who is he?

135
00:08:32,289 --> 00:08:33,970
Why can't I meet him?

136
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:40,559
Did Klao have a beef with Cherd
in the past?

137
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,909
What happened?

138
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:50,190
Were we friends?

139
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,870
Did I owe him money?

140
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:58,350
Did we date the same person?

141
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:02,520
By dating, I mean...

142
00:09:02,930 --> 00:09:03,970
Falling in love.

143
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:10,820
If not dating...

144
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:12,080
Someone in the talking stage?

145
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:17,370
A man?

146
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:22,130
Or...was it a woman?

147
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,680
Really?

148
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:32,370
That troublemaker and Klao
once fought over a woman, huh?

149
00:09:35,890 --> 00:09:37,560
Who was she?

150
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:40,110
Huh?

151
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:44,380
I know nothing of it, Master.

152
00:09:44,420 --> 00:09:45,930
I can offer you no further answer.

153
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,130
Guess I have to
look into it again myself, don't I?

154
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,310
Gosh.

155
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:57,210
And...

156
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:59,530
Phop told us to wait here, right?

157
00:10:02,570 --> 00:10:03,950
How upsetting!

158
00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:18,570
So that is how the matter stands.

159
00:10:21,150 --> 00:10:23,730
Pray accept my apologies
for the disturbance he caused,

160
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:26,910
and my thanks
for overseeing the commotion,

161
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:30,010
especially as it lies
beyond your usual jurisdiction.

162
00:10:31,990 --> 00:10:33,270
It is of no account.

163
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,510
Pray think nothing of it.

164
00:10:36,350 --> 00:10:38,420
I am beholden to him

165
00:10:38,450 --> 00:10:40,090
for coming to her aid.

166
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,050
Lord.

167
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:49,380
Forgive my intrusion,

168
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,550
but I find

169
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:57,410
Dear Klao's demeanor most peculiar.

170
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:01,020
Despite his enmity toward Cherd,

171
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:03,620
he regards them as if they were but strangers.

172
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,090
He treats even me with the same reserve.

173
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,330
What truly has taken hold of him?

174
00:11:12,730 --> 00:11:14,800
Surely,
the intent was but to provoke his temper.

175
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:20,250
But does that apply to me as well?

176
00:11:22,570 --> 00:11:24,450
Dear Klao's resentment toward him
must be so profound

177
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:26,710
that he has turned his anger upon you.

178
00:11:27,940 --> 00:11:29,440
Allow me to make amends for his conduct.

179
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:44,140
Any soul would pity Dear Klao,

180
00:11:45,770 --> 00:11:48,340
for Lord Preechapiban's judicial matter
was a crushing ordeal.

181
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:52,440
It is more than any son should bear,

182
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,570
especially one
in so precarious a state of mind.

183
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,610
I can well understand it.

184
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,150
This is getting too long.

185
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:17,390
What is there for those
Twin Phops to be chatting about?

186
00:12:19,930 --> 00:12:21,450
It's so hot out here.

187
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:27,820
I want a bottle of Ichitan so bad!

188
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:41,610
"I..."

189
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:42,980
I beg your pardon, Master?

190
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,210
You don't know what Ichitan is?

191
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:47,840
Oh...

192
00:12:48,470 --> 00:12:49,680
Right.

193
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:51,580
Uh...

194
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,070
It's tea.

195
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,170
Green tea.

196
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:56,710
It's refreshing
and keeps us on top of our game.

197
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:00,090
"On top of the game?"

198
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:01,800
Uh...

199
00:13:01,980 --> 00:13:04,690
It makes us feel full of beans.

200
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,300
Full of...

201
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:07,590
Beans?

202
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,930
What was that you said, Master?

203
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:11,420
Forget it.

204
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:14,490
By the way,

205
00:13:14,770 --> 00:13:16,320
do people in Ayutthaya

206
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:18,330
drink tea?

207
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:20,340
Are there any cafes

208
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,880
or tea shops here?

209
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,330
There is, indeed, a teahouse, Master.

210
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:28,090
It is Meng's.

211
00:13:28,660 --> 00:13:31,310
But they do not serve a tea full of beans.

212
00:13:31,490 --> 00:13:32,540
There is one?

213
00:13:33,170 --> 00:13:33,850
Cool!

214
00:13:33,930 --> 00:13:36,040
Let's go to the teahouse. Come on!

215
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:37,810
Oh, Master.

216
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:39,230
I shall remain here, Master.

217
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:41,370
I would not dare defy
the Lord's words ever again.

218
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:42,780
Heaven knows
how many strokes of the cane await me

219
00:13:42,810 --> 00:13:45,130
for escorting you here in secret.

220
00:13:46,070 --> 00:13:47,970
Until the lesson is well and truly learned,

221
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:53,340
so that you may never again
take him on such diversions.

222
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,520
Uh...

223
00:13:57,930 --> 00:14:00,500
Phop, don't blame him for this.

224
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:05,170
I was the one
who talked him into bringing me here.

225
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:08,320
Have you at last learned
to take responsibility for your actions?

226
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:10,890
Punish me all you want,

227
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:14,160
but please bring me to a cafe.

228
00:14:17,420 --> 00:14:19,050
I mean, the teahouse.

229
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:21,430
I'm so, so thirsty,

230
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:24,810
I might even drink canal water
just to quench it.

231
00:14:30,930 --> 00:14:33,250
Do not attempt to sway me
with such sly looks.

232
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:36,730
Chuay.

233
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:38,470
Remain here.

234
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,170
Come with me.

235
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:45,720
Remember this:

236
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:49,130
you are to go nowhere
unless it be with me, and me alone.

237
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:59,680
♫Stay right here♫

238
00:14:59,710 --> 00:15:03,400
♫I shall spend the time I hold so dearly♫

239
00:15:03,430 --> 00:15:07,880
♫And make the most of it when I see you♫

240
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:11,000
♫It makes my life so meaningful♫

241
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:12,670
Whoa.

242
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,460
This way.

243
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:16,590
Right this way.

244
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,440
Oh, my Lord.

245
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,680
Pray, step inside, my Lord.

246
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:29,620
"My Lord?"

247
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:31,920
Which lord do you mean, A-Chai?

248
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:35,770
There are so many lords in this land.

249
00:15:36,650 --> 00:15:38,030
Which one do you mean?

250
00:15:38,430 --> 00:15:39,430
Deary me...

251
00:15:39,660 --> 00:15:42,950
I wonder which lord it is... Ah!

252
00:15:42,990 --> 00:15:44,160
Lord Phop, is it not?

253
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:47,470
There is nothing illicit
in this establishment, my Lord.

254
00:15:47,510 --> 00:15:50,610
There are...
There are no thieves here.

255
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:53,450
There are no outlaws
or thieves inside, my Lord.

256
00:15:53,610 --> 00:15:55,240
I have not come to hunt down thieves;

257
00:15:55,570 --> 00:15:57,920
only to bring my brother for a cup of tea.

258
00:15:58,100 --> 00:15:59,730
What a relief...

259
00:16:00,570 --> 00:16:03,130
I bid welcome to Lord Phop's brother...

260
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:05,170
Good heavens!

261
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,210
Klao!

262
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,880
Klao...

263
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:11,050
Our teahouse does not offer spirits.

264
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:13,740
It has been ages since we last did so.

265
00:16:15,170 --> 00:16:16,170
Klao...

266
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:19,050
Take it easy, Master.

267
00:16:19,210 --> 00:16:22,020
You look rather bright and lively,

268
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,610
neither intoxicated nor aggressive.

269
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:26,170
Welcome to the teahouse.

270
00:16:26,730 --> 00:16:28,850
We have a tea
we would like you to try.

271
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:30,870
Do come inside for freshly brewed tea.

272
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,010
Pray, step inside.

273
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,370
Is he going to reduce my chairs to splinters?

274
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:40,210
Klao got so drunk that he caused trouble?

275
00:16:45,450 --> 00:16:48,130
Ah, it is ready.

276
00:16:48,170 --> 00:16:51,710
Da Hong Pao.

277
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,210
This is the tea.

278
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:55,860
Drinking it shall compel you
to utter the word

279
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,930
"Delicious!"

280
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,770
It is very delightful.

281
00:16:59,950 --> 00:17:02,890
It is the very tea favored by

282
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,980
the current Emperor himself.

283
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,050
This comes from Fujian.

284
00:17:09,329 --> 00:17:11,170
- Fujian?
- Mm.

285
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,440
It is a province

286
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:15,849
whose capital is Fuzhou.

287
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:19,540
This particular tea shall rejuvenate

288
00:17:19,569 --> 00:17:21,130
your soul,

289
00:17:21,190 --> 00:17:23,220
as if a bodhisattva's chant

290
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:26,530
were echoing within your heart.

291
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:44,130
Master.

292
00:17:44,970 --> 00:17:45,850
What was that?

293
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:48,070
What you heard
was the chant of a bodhisattva.

294
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:50,660
I merely wished to provide you
with a clearer perspective.

295
00:17:50,970 --> 00:17:52,450
It is as simple as that.

296
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:53,900
Steamed pork buns

297
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:57,870
- and freshly made mantou are here.
- Here.

298
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,750
My goodness!
To enjoy these together with tea…

299
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:01,970
Da...

300
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:08,050
- Hong Pao?
- Wonderful. Your memory is just as sharp.

301
00:18:08,090 --> 00:18:10,130
Too much drinking dulls your mind.

302
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:11,460
- It is my duty to take care of...
- Master,

303
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:12,790
- Huh?
- customers.

304
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,170
Foreigners are here.

305
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:18,050
Kindly enjoy the steamed buns
and Da Hong Pao while I am away.

306
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:22,100
Oh, welcome.

307
00:18:24,550 --> 00:18:27,170
If Master gets to talk to Muan,

308
00:18:27,450 --> 00:18:29,200
I bet it'd be a really fun time.

309
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:30,940
In that case,

310
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:32,530
who shall be their listener?

311
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:43,570
My God, there is no soul
in this country who commands in English.

312
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:46,290
Mark.

313
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:48,010
The fellow at that table,

314
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:51,250
- the one clad in black sleeves...
- Aye.

315
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:53,610
He serves as a constable in this quarter.

316
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,490
I once quarreled with a vendor who...

317
00:18:56,930 --> 00:18:59,350
claimed I had paid with a false coin.

318
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:03,370
Officer came. Poor fool
could scarcely understand a word!

319
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,700
Hold.

320
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:14,770
Methinks the young fellow doth watch us.

321
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:17,700
Quite a stare!

322
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:20,530
He understands, if not.

323
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:22,790
None of the Siamese do!

324
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:31,330
Good sirs.

325
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,660
If thou wouldst scorn an entire land,

326
00:19:34,690 --> 00:19:36,650
at least do so with wit.

327
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:40,470
Know this: we understand thee well.

328
00:19:40,710 --> 00:19:44,840
We simply find no joy in sparring words...

329
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:46,730
with fools.

330
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:53,990
He doth speak our tongue.

331
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:57,810
Aye,

332
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:01,390
and if thou wouldst have me use it harshly,

333
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:02,730
I can.

334
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,910
Hold thy tongue!

335
00:20:04,940 --> 00:20:07,150
Lest thou catch the leash!

336
00:20:07,550 --> 00:20:08,550
A leash?

337
00:20:09,620 --> 00:20:11,240
Art thou a cur then?

338
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:13,030
Nay... A bitch.

339
00:20:13,070 --> 00:20:15,920
- What said'st thou?!
- Hold, hold, hold.

340
00:20:19,010 --> 00:20:21,370
Dost thou not speak English?

341
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,590
Thai? Any tongue at all?

342
00:20:23,980 --> 00:20:25,450
Who now is the fool?

343
00:20:27,580 --> 00:20:30,770
Come. This is but noise
and madness. Let's away!

344
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:32,820
Do go.

345
00:20:34,060 --> 00:20:35,600
But mark me well:

346
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:39,010
speak not low of Siamese again.

347
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:43,210
We are thy equals. Remember that!

348
00:20:43,970 --> 00:20:47,070
My, my.
Surely I shall not forgot thy visage!

349
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:49,620
Huh...

350
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:55,480
- That's Nakun Phattanatada for you,
- My! You can speak their tongue?

351
00:20:55,510 --> 00:20:57,640
the top student in Shakespeare Studies.

352
00:21:02,660 --> 00:21:04,380
Wonderful, wonderful.

353
00:21:09,380 --> 00:21:11,830
What color is the banana
called in the Farangi tongue?

354
00:21:12,420 --> 00:21:14,190
Uh... Yellow!

355
00:21:16,430 --> 00:21:17,410
What about that fruit?

356
00:21:17,780 --> 00:21:18,870
Mango!

357
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:21,440
- What about that dessert?
- Khanom tako! Aha!

358
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:24,900
Not funny?

359
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:29,650
Your way of speaking Thai
is quite peculiar.

360
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:33,880
How is it, then,
that you speak the foreign tongue so fluently?

361
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,170
Where did you acquire such skill?

362
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:39,680
Was it in Phichit as well?

363
00:21:41,370 --> 00:21:42,490
Uh...

364
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:44,530
I learned it in Phichit, my Lord.

365
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:52,490
I shouldn't have said that.

366
00:21:52,710 --> 00:21:55,320
He has even more reason
to be suspicious now.

367
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:58,790
The Farangi soldiers
we had just encountered...

368
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:01,670
I once attempted to mediate
a dispute between one of them and a vendor.

369
00:22:01,890 --> 00:22:04,300
However, with no one
to bridge the language gap,

370
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,890
both sides departed
equally dissatisfied and misunderstood.

371
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,730
In due time,
you shall teach me this foreign tongue.

372
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,790
Were I literate in the language,

373
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:18,860
I could do so much more for our people.

374
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:26,960
Master Klao.

375
00:22:27,490 --> 00:22:30,790
How was your time
at the teahouse, Master Klao?

376
00:22:30,820 --> 00:22:31,950
You look rather delighted.

377
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:33,560
Trouble upon trouble.

378
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:36,000
Do not venture out on your own again.

379
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:38,880
Is it not clear
how peril lurks around every corner?

380
00:22:40,140 --> 00:22:41,290
What peril?

381
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,190
My time in Phichit
was even more dangerous.

382
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:44,860
I saw giant crocodiles.

383
00:22:45,020 --> 00:22:46,540
Have you ever heard of Chalawan?

384
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,600
Master Klao.

385
00:22:48,890 --> 00:22:50,650
Who is Charles Le Wand?

386
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:52,370
Gosh...

387
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:55,010
That is not the kind of danger
I was referring to.

388
00:22:55,410 --> 00:22:57,250
I was speaking of the ruffians.

389
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:00,620
Perhaps you are unaware that

390
00:23:01,270 --> 00:23:03,290
you have more adversaries
than you can fathom.

391
00:23:04,580 --> 00:23:05,580
But...

392
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:09,110
This is bringing back
so many of my memories.

393
00:23:11,230 --> 00:23:13,080
Even so, the risk
outweighs any possible gain.

394
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,990
It is well that
Lord Harn intervened in time.

395
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:19,210
Without him, you could have ended up
in another dispute with Cherd.

396
00:23:26,570 --> 00:23:28,070
I am not quarreling with you.

397
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,180
I am concerned for your safety.

398
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:34,120
I already know that.

399
00:23:36,380 --> 00:23:37,650
That said, step into the boat.

400
00:24:03,860 --> 00:24:05,350
If everything is in order,
let us set sail.

401
00:24:05,530 --> 00:24:06,330
Yes, my Lord.

402
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:12,810
Fortune teller? Wait, it's her!

403
00:24:13,490 --> 00:24:14,810
Be wary, Master Klao.

404
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:18,010
Chuay, leave without me.
Let me go talk to her.

405
00:24:20,170 --> 00:24:21,560
Where is this fortune teller of yours?

406
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:23,490
- I have yet to see a single soul.
- She's...

407
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:30,480
But I...

408
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:38,270
Jom...

409
00:24:57,550 --> 00:24:58,580
What is it that catches your eye?

410
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:01,890
Is there something upon my face?

411
00:25:07,270 --> 00:25:09,220
No, not at all...

412
00:25:09,580 --> 00:25:12,010
Are you making herbal remedies?

413
00:25:12,390 --> 00:25:13,480
Yes, of course.

414
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:16,230
Did you take this for washing clothes?

415
00:25:17,210 --> 00:25:19,010
Have you gone mad, like Klao has?

416
00:25:20,290 --> 00:25:22,180
I was but making conversation.

417
00:25:22,670 --> 00:25:23,670
Uh...

418
00:25:24,950 --> 00:25:27,430
Have there been many patients today?

419
00:25:27,530 --> 00:25:29,140
Are you exhausted, Jom?

420
00:25:29,630 --> 00:25:32,570
To what end
do you repeat these same questions?

421
00:25:33,270 --> 00:25:36,810
No reason, really.
I have brought you some food.

422
00:25:37,110 --> 00:25:40,230
I feared you might go without food again.

423
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:43,370
Always tending to my needs...

424
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:46,590
Have you no other duties to attend to?

425
00:25:47,580 --> 00:25:51,110
I finished all my household chores
this morning.

426
00:25:56,970 --> 00:25:57,970
Kaew.

427
00:25:59,340 --> 00:26:02,330
You are a man.
You should be out there, making your way

428
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:04,770
for the sake of those at home.

429
00:26:08,310 --> 00:26:11,490
There is so much to be done here,

430
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:13,170
and we are short-handed.

431
00:26:13,730 --> 00:26:15,450
You are the son of a high lord.

432
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:17,390
Be strong and courageous,

433
00:26:18,580 --> 00:26:20,690
so that you may protect your family.

434
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:56,280
Now then, will you give me my meal,

435
00:26:56,460 --> 00:26:58,570
or must I drink your tears instead?

436
00:27:04,830 --> 00:27:06,320
So you will eat, then?

437
00:27:06,870 --> 00:27:07,770
Mhm.

438
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:10,150
Put it on a plate for me.

439
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:14,510
If there is no work to be done,

440
00:27:14,980 --> 00:27:16,730
then come and help me
fashion these herbal remedies.

441
00:27:50,850 --> 00:27:53,890
Cherd? My enemy? We fought over a girl?

442
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:58,970
Help me!

443
00:27:59,770 --> 00:28:00,690
Klao!

444
00:28:07,010 --> 00:28:09,690
Or is there something else?

445
00:28:17,450 --> 00:28:20,540
Clinging to your master's side?
Soon enough, your wife might be gone.

446
00:28:21,170 --> 00:28:22,570
Watch over her for me, then.

447
00:28:22,670 --> 00:28:24,190
I am too concerned about my master.

448
00:28:24,470 --> 00:28:26,290
Chuay, your master is no longer a child.

449
00:28:26,430 --> 00:28:28,050
Why must you watch over him so intently?

450
00:28:28,450 --> 00:28:31,310
Then what is your excuse for loitering here
and staring me down like this?

451
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:42,180
Lord Harn is Phop's colleague,
or is there something more?

452
00:28:42,450 --> 00:28:45,190
You look rather bright and lively,

453
00:28:45,230 --> 00:28:47,800
neither intoxicated nor aggressive.

454
00:28:54,510 --> 00:28:57,880
Meng knew that Klao was an alcoholic.

455
00:29:02,300 --> 00:29:04,950
An outburst at the teahouse?

456
00:29:05,050 --> 00:29:08,270
Was it related to Cherd or something?

457
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,450
Is he refusing to eat?

458
00:29:21,660 --> 00:29:25,800
My knuckles are sore from all the knocking,
yet he simply refuses to come out, my Lord.

459
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,630
And what's the deal with
the fortune teller?

460
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:44,760
Is she just a look-alike?

461
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:49,620
Or...

462
00:29:50,150 --> 00:29:52,340
Do you believe in multiple lifetimes?

463
00:29:54,130 --> 00:29:55,780
Reincarnation?

464
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:03,050
No! That's insane. That's impossible.

465
00:30:08,810 --> 00:30:11,690
Traveling through time myself

466
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:14,130
also sounds impossible.

467
00:30:17,780 --> 00:30:19,130
Be careful, Nakun.

468
00:30:19,420 --> 00:30:22,650
In the world of time travel literature,

469
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:26,770
we cannot always rely on logic.

470
00:30:26,970 --> 00:30:31,180
It might reflect something

471
00:30:31,210 --> 00:30:33,240
that lies deep within.

472
00:30:57,700 --> 00:30:58,820
How the hell did she get here?

473
00:31:03,310 --> 00:31:04,310
Fortune teller?

474
00:31:04,670 --> 00:31:05,670
It really is you, isn't it?

475
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,440
No.

476
00:31:08,110 --> 00:31:09,810
I tell no fortunes.

477
00:31:11,290 --> 00:31:12,770
Come on. Stop playing around.

478
00:31:15,070 --> 00:31:16,070
Hey.

479
00:31:16,340 --> 00:31:18,330
It's just the two of us now.

480
00:31:18,670 --> 00:31:20,260
No need to hide your true self.

481
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:23,890
Did you also travel through time with me,

482
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:28,890
or did you reincarnate
as Fortune Teller Rattikarn?

483
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:30,370
Hey.

484
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:32,010
Answer me.

485
00:31:33,210 --> 00:31:34,510
Rattikarn!

486
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:36,720
Dark and cold!

487
00:31:37,190 --> 00:31:40,010
Such agony.

488
00:31:40,330 --> 00:31:44,130
Can you not speak in riddles?
Say something easy to understand.

489
00:31:44,730 --> 00:31:45,730
Help.

490
00:31:51,270 --> 00:31:52,530
Can't breathe!

491
00:31:53,830 --> 00:31:56,060
Dear Klao's soul...

492
00:31:57,170 --> 00:31:59,210
It is in agony.

493
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:01,850
No one is coming to help.

494
00:32:08,430 --> 00:32:09,390
Young man.

495
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:13,950
What brings you to this place?

496
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:16,750
Did the forest lead you astray?

497
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:21,470
Dear Klao's soul?

498
00:32:25,010 --> 00:32:27,590
So is Klao really dead?

499
00:32:45,490 --> 00:32:47,370
You came out and ate at last,

500
00:32:48,260 --> 00:32:49,610
you grumpy cat.

501
00:33:34,290 --> 00:33:36,050
An earthquake!
The Great Fish has turned!

502
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:49,380
Why are you getting emotional
in Klao's place again, Nakun?

503
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:51,450
Klao! Klao!!

504
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:53,330
What seems to be the trouble?

505
00:33:53,590 --> 00:33:54,810
What brings these tears?

506
00:33:55,030 --> 00:33:56,330
What has the Oracle done to you?

507
00:33:57,620 --> 00:33:59,170
What have you done unto my Brother?!

508
00:33:59,410 --> 00:34:01,990
I have yet to do anything.

509
00:34:03,590 --> 00:34:06,690
What is all this commotion, Phop?
I can hear it from the front of the manor.

510
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,850
As if causing trouble in the capital
were not enough,

511
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,650
the Oracle has followed us to our manor

512
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:17,550
and brought him to tears.

513
00:34:18,780 --> 00:34:21,610
No, I have done nothing.

514
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,870
Phop.

515
00:34:27,010 --> 00:34:31,210
Take pity on her,
for she has gone mad, as Klao has.

516
00:34:34,850 --> 00:34:36,409
I know you mean no harm.

517
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:40,750
Upon seeing him,
you likely felt the urge to offer a prophecy,

518
00:34:40,790 --> 00:34:42,290
hoping to be of some help, did you not?

519
00:34:43,070 --> 00:34:44,070
Help...

520
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:46,929
Yes, I wish to help him.

521
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:49,190
Here.

522
00:34:49,510 --> 00:34:51,850
Consider this your payment.

523
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,760
It is time for you
to head back to your manor.

524
00:34:59,930 --> 00:35:01,850
I am deeply grateful to you, my Lady.

525
00:35:13,190 --> 00:35:16,360
In some matters,
a calm approach is far more effective

526
00:35:16,390 --> 00:35:19,650
than a loud outburst, Phop.

527
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:32,900
The Oracle is a pitiful soul.

528
00:35:33,290 --> 00:35:36,250
She was cast out of the palace
merely for being different in nature.

529
00:35:37,110 --> 00:35:39,650
She appears deranged now,

530
00:35:39,810 --> 00:35:42,250
for she has been beaten senseless.

531
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:45,520
Senselessly beaten...

532
00:35:47,780 --> 00:35:49,170
Just like what they did to my father.

533
00:35:50,330 --> 00:35:51,510
You are correct.

534
00:35:52,450 --> 00:35:53,860
Before that cruel punishment,

535
00:35:54,060 --> 00:35:55,890
her prophecies were without equal.

536
00:35:57,240 --> 00:36:00,310
A tragedy of fate and past karma,

537
00:36:00,500 --> 00:36:02,710
that she should suffer
such cruel punishment and lose her mind.

538
00:36:03,890 --> 00:36:04,890
Phop...

539
00:36:06,170 --> 00:36:07,970
do not hold such bitterness against her.

540
00:36:09,170 --> 00:36:11,090
I hold nothing against her.

541
00:36:12,010 --> 00:36:15,170
I am merely displeased
that she made him cry.

542
00:36:17,850 --> 00:36:19,090
No, Phop.

543
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:23,550
I cried on my own.

544
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,550
Oh...

545
00:36:31,450 --> 00:36:34,010
My body aches so.
Age is finally catching up with me.

546
00:36:34,490 --> 00:36:37,610
I have spent
the better part of the day with my friends.

547
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:39,780
Now, I shall retire to rest.

548
00:36:39,810 --> 00:36:41,970
Be gentle with him, will you?

549
00:36:42,790 --> 00:36:43,690
Understood.

550
00:36:45,580 --> 00:36:46,610
Sai.

551
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:48,970
Escort me.

552
00:37:12,890 --> 00:37:14,470
- Say what you must....
- Go ahead and ask.

553
00:37:21,660 --> 00:37:24,610
I guess we'll each take turns
asking questions.

554
00:37:25,490 --> 00:37:26,690
You go first.

555
00:37:27,890 --> 00:37:28,890
Certainly.

556
00:37:33,370 --> 00:37:35,730
You told everyone
that you had lost your memory.

557
00:37:36,750 --> 00:37:40,770
You have no recollection of me
or of anyone in this manor.

558
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:44,010
And yet, that Oracle...

559
00:37:44,710 --> 00:37:46,400
You remember her perfectly well,

560
00:37:46,870 --> 00:37:49,090
and you seemed rather desperate to meet her.

561
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:50,560
Why is it so?

562
00:37:51,610 --> 00:37:53,330
Are you two acquainted?

563
00:37:55,540 --> 00:37:58,130
Why don't you want me
to talk to her that much?

564
00:38:00,520 --> 00:38:02,050
We agreed to exchange questions,

565
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,690
yet you have not answered mine.

566
00:38:05,910 --> 00:38:09,890
I suggested we exchange questions,

567
00:38:10,250 --> 00:38:12,730
but I didn't say
we had to take turns answering them.

568
00:38:13,110 --> 00:38:14,250
Klao.

569
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:18,960
Well...

570
00:38:19,950 --> 00:38:22,170
When I was in Phichit,

571
00:38:22,930 --> 00:38:26,040
I met someone...

572
00:38:27,120 --> 00:38:28,610
who looked like her.

573
00:38:29,770 --> 00:38:33,090
But...I'm not sure whether

574
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:37,010
she was the same person I met.

575
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:43,250
You began to cry
as soon as you learned the truth?

576
00:38:48,810 --> 00:38:51,970
It is your turn.
What is it that you wish to know?

577
00:38:53,750 --> 00:38:56,570
You don't want me to talk to her
because she's weird?

578
00:38:57,580 --> 00:38:58,730
I mean, deranged.

579
00:39:00,010 --> 00:39:01,010
And...

580
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:03,610
the answer had better not be,

581
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:06,290
"I'm concerned about you."

582
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:11,360
You there.

583
00:39:12,020 --> 00:39:15,170
Tell Chuay to ready my vessel.

584
00:39:15,470 --> 00:39:17,570
I intend to take him elsewhere.

585
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:18,890
Yes, my Lord.

586
00:39:22,390 --> 00:39:23,390
Where to?

587
00:39:26,930 --> 00:39:28,250
To seek the truth.

588
00:39:46,730 --> 00:39:47,890
Where is Jom?

589
00:39:51,370 --> 00:39:52,610
Jom.

590
00:39:52,980 --> 00:39:54,210
Jom...

591
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,510
I shall take these herbal remedies and...

592
00:40:16,950 --> 00:40:17,950
Jom.

593
00:40:18,820 --> 00:40:20,820
Why must you bathe
at this hour of all times?

594
00:40:32,570 --> 00:40:35,960
I have been at work all day
and am covered in sweat.

595
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:37,730
Am I not to be permitted a bath?

596
00:40:43,170 --> 00:40:44,450
And why are you hiding?

597
00:40:44,770 --> 00:40:46,810
Come down and speak with me properly
if there is aught to discuss.

598
00:40:48,810 --> 00:40:49,990
It is nothing.

599
00:40:51,050 --> 00:40:53,370
I came only to tell you
that I am returning.

600
00:40:54,490 --> 00:40:55,850
Take your time with your bath.

601
00:40:56,460 --> 00:40:58,370
I shall wait for you upstairs.

602
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:02,490
Come and wait for me at the pier at once.

603
00:41:03,130 --> 00:41:04,750
What cause have you for embarrassment?

604
00:41:41,380 --> 00:41:42,650
Come closer.

605
00:41:56,890 --> 00:41:59,010
Have the herbal remedies been set
in their proper cabinet?

606
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:02,780
Yes, the fresh ones
are still laid out to dry.

607
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:06,110
The dried herbs are kept
in the leftmost cabinet within the manor.

608
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:09,050
Look at me when you address me.

609
00:42:28,080 --> 00:42:29,450
Are you shy with me?

610
00:42:31,990 --> 00:42:33,450
We are both men.

611
00:42:33,690 --> 00:42:35,130
What is there to be shy about,

612
00:42:38,340 --> 00:42:40,890
- apart from...
- No, I am not.

613
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,380
Very well.

614
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,050
Then look well upon me.

615
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,370
Jom.

616
00:42:58,060 --> 00:42:59,170
As I thought.

617
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:02,410
You are thinking of something wicked,
are you not, Kaew?

618
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,000
Jom.

619
00:43:13,060 --> 00:43:16,290
Do you despise me so greatly
that you would act thus?

620
00:43:18,790 --> 00:43:19,790
No.

621
00:43:21,080 --> 00:43:22,970
I was but jesting with you,
as friends often do.

622
00:43:28,010 --> 00:43:29,970
There is no need for you
to trouble yourself over the matter.

623
00:44:45,120 --> 00:44:46,350
Why are we here?

624
00:44:49,340 --> 00:44:51,850
We used to play here in our childhood days.

625
00:44:52,740 --> 00:44:54,360
Oh...

626
00:45:02,070 --> 00:45:03,170
Klao!

627
00:45:03,970 --> 00:45:05,670
Where might you be, Klao?!

628
00:45:06,560 --> 00:45:08,170
Come out, will you not, Klao?

629
00:45:09,170 --> 00:45:12,360
Where are you?
Where are you hiding, Klao?!

630
00:45:15,410 --> 00:45:16,490
Klao!!

631
00:45:18,100 --> 00:45:20,070
Klao! Where are you?

632
00:45:24,460 --> 00:45:26,660
Klao, wake up.

633
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:28,100
Klao...

634
00:45:37,710 --> 00:45:41,290
You have lost.
You have failed to find me.

635
00:45:43,250 --> 00:45:46,630
Goodness, you were here all along,
hiding and sleeping

636
00:45:46,740 --> 00:45:48,290
without a sound.

637
00:45:48,740 --> 00:45:50,500
How could you expect me to find you at all?

638
00:45:50,700 --> 00:45:52,090
Do not blame me for this.

639
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:54,250
It was you who could not find me.

640
00:45:54,340 --> 00:45:56,890
Fine. I gave up.

641
00:45:57,920 --> 00:45:58,920
Come.

642
00:45:59,760 --> 00:46:01,490
The sun is about to set.

643
00:46:02,090 --> 00:46:03,090
Let us return.

644
00:46:11,790 --> 00:46:14,850
Phop... Phop! Take a look.

645
00:46:15,470 --> 00:46:18,090
What are those things
that fly so high in the sky?

646
00:46:18,510 --> 00:46:21,850
Oh, those are paper kites.

647
00:46:24,860 --> 00:46:28,450
One day, I shall tie myself to a kite

648
00:46:29,220 --> 00:46:31,370
and soar high in the sky.

649
00:46:31,510 --> 00:46:33,410
Help make it come true, will you?

650
00:46:34,510 --> 00:46:35,670
Of course.

651
00:46:49,670 --> 00:46:50,670
Phop.

652
00:46:53,370 --> 00:46:56,550
Where have you been taking him
until this hour of night?

653
00:46:57,000 --> 00:47:00,920
I only took him out
to play in the rice fields, Mother.

654
00:47:01,110 --> 00:47:03,910
I was the one
who insisted that he go out to play,

655
00:47:04,100 --> 00:47:05,660
and I accidentally fell asleep.

656
00:47:05,850 --> 00:47:07,810
He bears no fault in this, Aunt.

657
00:47:08,190 --> 00:47:10,650
And did you both
enjoy yourselves while playing together?

658
00:47:10,880 --> 00:47:11,590
We did.

659
00:47:11,620 --> 00:47:13,350
- Yes, we did.
- We played hide and seek.

660
00:47:13,380 --> 00:47:16,170
We also saw the farmers flying paper kites.

661
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:18,040
Good.

662
00:47:18,830 --> 00:47:20,530
You shared joy together,

663
00:47:21,020 --> 00:47:24,390
so you must likewise
stand together through hardship.

664
00:47:55,190 --> 00:47:57,590
Next time, let this be a reminder
to look out for each other

665
00:47:57,920 --> 00:48:00,090
and not lose track of time.

666
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:02,500
- Understood.
- Yes, Mother.

667
00:48:08,960 --> 00:48:10,890
Each time Mother punished you,

668
00:48:11,420 --> 00:48:13,450
my heart ached for you.

669
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:16,190
Could I take the blows in your stead,
I truly would.

670
00:48:21,870 --> 00:48:23,350
And yet,

671
00:48:24,430 --> 00:48:26,290
we return here often,

672
00:48:28,650 --> 00:48:30,280
for the evening view

673
00:48:30,900 --> 00:48:32,930
is more beautiful than anywhere else.

674
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:36,920
Now that we are grown,

675
00:48:37,810 --> 00:48:39,890
whenever your heart is troubled,

676
00:48:43,840 --> 00:48:46,270
I know exactly where to find you.

677
00:48:55,270 --> 00:48:57,310
I had a feeling
I should find you hiding here.

678
00:49:00,300 --> 00:49:02,010
You already know, do you not?

679
00:49:04,530 --> 00:49:06,470
I must accompany Father to Phichit.

680
00:49:13,090 --> 00:49:14,770
I have no desire to depart with him.

681
00:49:15,770 --> 00:49:17,590
The city feels far too distant from here.

682
00:49:19,870 --> 00:49:21,850
I do not wish to be parted from you.

683
00:49:29,410 --> 00:49:30,970
Who says it is too distant from here?

684
00:49:33,190 --> 00:49:35,070
Traveling by merchant ship,

685
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:37,140
it should take me there
in no more than three weeks.

686
00:49:37,420 --> 00:49:39,110
Three full weeks.

687
00:49:41,180 --> 00:49:43,420
And you will be part of the city patrol.

688
00:49:45,370 --> 00:49:49,650
How can you expect to find the time
to come see me as far as Phichit?

689
00:49:52,970 --> 00:49:54,600
Stay in Phichit

690
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:57,050
and devote yourself to your education.

691
00:49:57,790 --> 00:50:01,060
Perhaps next year you could take the exam
and join the patrol with me?

692
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:04,760
I would rather not.

693
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:07,410
I have never had any ambition.

694
00:50:08,290 --> 00:50:09,970
And what is it you wish to become?

695
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:14,900
I do not exactly know.

696
00:50:18,400 --> 00:50:20,100
I only know one thing:

697
00:50:23,360 --> 00:50:25,690
I am certain of my desire
to remain here with you.

698
00:50:27,370 --> 00:50:28,470
That is all.

699
00:50:37,960 --> 00:50:39,820
Every evening while you were gone,

700
00:50:40,600 --> 00:50:42,450
I came here to wait for you,

701
00:50:43,770 --> 00:50:45,750
believing that you would one day return.

702
00:50:48,060 --> 00:50:50,350
And at last, I truly found you again.

703
00:50:59,060 --> 00:51:02,650
To watch the sun fade beyond the horizon
with you again

704
00:51:04,090 --> 00:51:06,810
is all I ever wished for in this world.

705
00:51:27,860 --> 00:51:30,210
If anything is weighing on your heart,
I am here to listen.

706
00:51:30,940 --> 00:51:33,100
I shall simply listen, without judgment.

707
00:51:34,310 --> 00:51:36,970
I shall not judge nor dictate your choices.

708
00:51:38,350 --> 00:51:40,890
And should you need my assistance,
I remain entirely at your service.

709
00:51:56,490 --> 00:51:58,850
There is no rush,
should you not yet be ready.

710
00:51:59,850 --> 00:52:01,450
But remember this:

711
00:52:02,100 --> 00:52:04,370
I shall always be here,
standing by your side.

712
00:52:18,180 --> 00:52:19,490
Let us return.

713
00:52:20,660 --> 00:52:22,250
Dusk draws near.

714
00:53:28,190 --> 00:53:29,450
Please let me go.

715
00:53:29,660 --> 00:53:30,970
I'm fine now.

716
00:53:31,370 --> 00:53:32,370
No.

717
00:53:33,110 --> 00:53:35,530
I shall not let you slip away
from my grasp again.

718
00:53:36,910 --> 00:53:38,970
I shall forever take care of you, my Klao.

719
00:54:09,370 --> 00:54:12,050
[What is this feeling?]

720
00:54:12,210 --> 00:54:14,470
What is this? What's happening?

721
00:54:14,630 --> 00:54:16,210
Why do I feel this way?

722
00:54:16,280 --> 00:54:18,170
I've never felt this way before.

723
00:54:18,280 --> 00:54:20,090
What's going on?

724
00:54:21,690 --> 00:54:22,690
Hands up!

725
00:54:22,750 --> 00:54:25,010
Hands ready? In three and four!

726
00:54:28,750 --> 00:54:30,730
Thee, your posture is wrong.

727
00:54:35,790 --> 00:54:37,370
Make it stronger.

728
00:54:42,050 --> 00:54:43,890
Well done, Nakun.

729
00:54:45,470 --> 00:54:47,090
What a lovely smile you've got.

730
00:54:48,270 --> 00:54:50,890
A little bit higher, okay?

731
00:54:51,410 --> 00:54:52,410
Okay.

732
00:54:55,850 --> 00:54:56,850
Nakun.

733
00:54:57,170 --> 00:54:59,330
I think Nam Ngio is into you.

734
00:54:59,880 --> 00:55:01,160
What the hell are you on about?

735
00:55:01,920 --> 00:55:03,390
She only compliments you.

736
00:55:03,940 --> 00:55:07,050
You like her?
I can give you her contact details.

737
00:55:07,370 --> 00:55:11,050
I'm good. I can help your face
meet the ground. Want me to?

738
00:55:12,190 --> 00:55:13,490
Since junior high school,

739
00:55:14,220 --> 00:55:16,630
I've never seen you date anyone.

740
00:55:17,260 --> 00:55:18,680
So have you.

741
00:55:18,950 --> 00:55:20,810
Yet the world didn't end, did it?

742
00:55:21,140 --> 00:55:25,850
Don't you ever get
that butterfly feeling in your stomach?

743
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:29,090
No, all I feel in my stomach
is the digestive juices.

744
00:55:29,120 --> 00:55:31,260
It's overflowing, and it's not stopping.

745
00:55:32,930 --> 00:55:35,890
Haven't you ever felt excited
looking at someone?

746
00:55:37,180 --> 00:55:38,320
Is this what it's like

747
00:55:39,060 --> 00:55:42,690
to have butterflies in my stomach?

748
00:55:43,710 --> 00:55:45,770
Have I actually gotten excited?

749
00:55:46,800 --> 00:55:49,020
I have a crush on...

750
00:55:49,360 --> 00:55:51,190
that deadpan-looking guy?

751
00:55:51,890 --> 00:55:53,050
I can't.

752
00:55:53,410 --> 00:55:54,970
Is this an obstacle

753
00:55:55,680 --> 00:55:58,890
stopping me from completing my mission?

754
00:55:59,380 --> 00:56:01,770
I shall not let you slip away
from my grasp again.

755
00:56:03,090 --> 00:56:05,210
I shall forever take care of you, my Klao.

756
00:56:13,710 --> 00:56:15,660
"My Klao..."

757
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:23,450
It's not "my Nakun," alright?

758
00:56:32,680 --> 00:56:34,600
Ah, you come at a perfect time.

759
00:56:42,750 --> 00:56:44,120
Klao.

760
00:56:44,760 --> 00:56:46,000
So you are already acquainted?

761
00:56:47,330 --> 00:56:50,330
He met Varna at the market only a day ago.

762
00:56:50,370 --> 00:56:52,140
Mm...

763
00:56:52,410 --> 00:56:54,160
This is High Lord Soontrapinit,

764
00:56:54,370 --> 00:56:56,710
father of Lord Harn,
whom you have met.

765
00:56:57,110 --> 00:56:59,120
He is also the uncle of Varna.

766
00:57:01,040 --> 00:57:02,480
Pray, do him your respects.

767
00:57:03,590 --> 00:57:07,000
Oh, is he Dear Klao,
the son of Lord Preechapiban?

768
00:57:07,030 --> 00:57:07,840
Mhm.

769
00:57:07,870 --> 00:57:09,640
Oh, do join us.

770
00:57:11,060 --> 00:57:12,120
Mm.

771
00:57:15,490 --> 00:57:16,490
Oh...

772
00:57:16,760 --> 00:57:19,560
I have brought
a rather large collection of gifts from Lavo.

773
00:57:22,520 --> 00:57:25,610
Pray offer my thanks
to High Lord Dech Kraisor.

774
00:57:25,640 --> 00:57:26,580
Mm.

775
00:57:26,610 --> 00:57:30,000
But next time,
pray do not feel obliged to bring so much.

776
00:57:30,240 --> 00:57:33,340
I would not wish for our cook to be disheartened,
as she is quite sensitive.

777
00:57:35,100 --> 00:57:36,000
Is that so?

778
00:57:40,540 --> 00:57:41,680
Certainly not.

779
00:57:41,810 --> 00:57:43,360
After all,

780
00:57:43,900 --> 00:57:48,040
we shall soon be family.

781
00:57:53,340 --> 00:57:55,840
Come, the feast awaits.

782
00:58:10,020 --> 00:58:11,650
He's about to get married.

783
00:58:12,200 --> 00:58:14,660
Hold back your thoughts and feelings.

784
00:58:17,720 --> 00:58:20,550
Complete the mission and return home.

785
00:58:21,200 --> 00:58:23,680
You'd be better off
quitting the game before it starts, Nakun!

786
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:55,660
Klao, do kindly come
and enjoy this with me.

787
00:58:57,520 --> 00:58:59,500
Klao, I should like to see
the swordplay of Phichit.

788
00:58:59,540 --> 00:59:00,800
Pray, let me see your art.

789
00:59:05,520 --> 00:59:08,630
This is the house of pleasure.

790
00:59:08,720 --> 00:59:13,740
What brings a gentleman such as youself
to a place like this, Klao?

791
00:59:13,790 --> 00:59:15,170
I can no longer wait.

792
00:59:15,640 --> 00:59:18,650
By now, Phop must be terribly worried.

793
00:59:20,000 --> 00:59:28,270
♫Even though we shed tears
for all we've been through,♫

794
00:59:28,340 --> 00:59:31,990
♫I shall love you as I always have,♫

795
00:59:32,060 --> 00:59:39,720
♫And never again will we cut ties loose♫

796
00:59:49,760 --> 00:59:53,280
♫Even though we shed tears♫

797
00:59:53,310 --> 00:59:58,150
♫for all we've been through,♫

798
00:59:58,180 --> 01:00:01,840
♫I shall love you as I always have,♫

799
01:00:01,870 --> 01:00:14,120
♫And never again will we cut ties loose♫

800
01:00:15,280 --> 01:00:19,360
[Love Upon a Time Series]

